A word is considered valid if:
It contains a minimum of 3 characters.
It contains only digits (0-9), and English letters (uppercase and lowercase).
It includes at least one vowel.
It includes at least one consonant.
You are given a string word.
Return true if word is valid, otherwise, return false.

SOURCE CODE:

bool isValid(char* word)
{
    int l=strlen(word);
    if(l<3)
        return false;
    int i=0;
    int vowel=0;
    int consonent=0;
    for (int i = 0; word[i] != '\0'; i++)
    {
        if(word[i]=='@' ||word[i]=='#'||word[i]=='$'||word[i]=='*'||word[i]=='&'||word[i]=='^'||word[i]=='%')
        {
            return false;
        }
        if((word[i]>='0' && word[i]<='9') || (word[i]>='a' && word[i]<='z') || (word[i]>='A' && word[i]<='Z'))
        {
            if(word[i]=='a'||word[i]=='e'||word[i]=='i'||word[i]=='o'||word[i]=='u'||word[i]=='A'||
            word[i]=='E'||word[i]=='I'||word[i]=='O'||word[i]=='U')
            {
                vowel=1;
            }
         else
         {
            if(!(word[i]>='0' && word[i]<='9'))
            {
                 consonent=1;
            }
         } 
         

        }
    }
    
    if(vowel==1 && consonent==1)
        return 1;

    return 0;   
}
OUTPUT:

Example 1:
Input: word = "234Adas"
Output: true
Explanation:
This word satisfies the conditions.

Example 2:
Input: word = "b3"
Output: false
Explanation:
The length of this word is fewer than 3, and does not have a vowel.

Example 3:
Input: word = "a3$e"
Output: false
Explanation:
This word contains a '$' character and does not have a consonant.
